{"title_page": "Ranisankail Upazila", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name           = Ranisankail\n| native_name             = \u09b0\u09be\u09a3\u09c0\u09b6\u0982\u0995\u09c8\u09b2\n| settlement_type         = [[Upazilas of Bangladesh|Upazila]]\n| image_skyline           =\n| imagesize               =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = Skyline of Ranisonkail, Bangladesh\n| pushpin_map             = Bangladesh\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Bangladesh\n| coordinates             = {{coord|25|{{#expr:.8875*60 round 1}}|N|88|{{#expr:.2514*60 round 1}}|E|type:adm3rd|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|Bangladesh}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Divisions of Bangladesh|Division]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Districts of Bangladesh|District]]\n| subdivision_type3       = <!-- Capital -->\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Rangpur Division]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Thakurgaon District]]\n| subdivision_name3       =\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| leader_title1           =\n| leader_name1            =\n| area_total_km2          = 287.59\n| area_metro_km2          =\n| elevation_m             =\n| elevation_ft            =\n| population_total        = 156107\n| population_as_of        = 1991\n| population_footnotes    =\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| postal_code_type        =\n| postal_code             =\n| website                 = {{URL|http://ranisankail.thakurgaon.gov.bd/}}\n| footnotes               =\n| timezone                = [[Bangladesh Standard Time|BST]]\n| utc_offset              = +6\n}}\n'''Ranisankail''' ({{lang-bn|\u09b0\u09be\u09a3\u09c0\u09b6\u0982\u0995\u09c8\u09b2}}) is an [[Upazila]] of [[Thakurgaon District]] in the Division of [[Rangpur Division|Rangpur]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name=Banglapedia>{{citation \n|author=Abu Md. Iqbal Rumi Shah\n|chapter=Ranisankail Upazila \n|chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Ranisankail_Upazila\n|title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |editor=Sirajul Islam and Ahmed A. Jamal |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]] |year=2012 |edition=Second}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nRanisankail is one of the ancient areas of [[Bengal]]. It lies in the North-east corner of Bangladesh and has a total area of 287.59&nbsp;km\u00b2. It lies about 480&nbsp;km from [[Dhaka]], the capital City of Bangladesh. The main rivers flowing through Ranisankail are the Kulic, Nagar, and Timai rivers. Land use total: cultivable land, 22405.09 hectares; fallow land, 6115.74; single crop, 30%, double crop, 55%; and treble crop 15%; cultivable land under irrigation, 69%.\n\nRanisankail upazila is bounded by [[Baliadangi Upazila|Baliadangi]] and [[Thakurgaon Sadar Upazila|Thakurgaon Sadar]] upazilas on the north, Thakurgaon Sadar upazila on the east, [[Hemtabad]] [[Community development block in India|CD block]] in Uttar Dinajpur district, West Bengal, India, on the south and [[Haripur Upazila]] on the west.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Ranisankail_Upazila |title = Ranisankail Upazila|publisher= Banglapedia | accessdate = 6 January 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url =  http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_A/19/1904_PART_A_DCHB_UTTAR%20DINAJPUR.pdf |title =  District Census Handbook Uttar Dinajpur, Series 20, Part XII A | work= Map of Uttar Dinajpur district on the fifth page |publisher= Directorate of Census Operations, West Bengal  | accessdate = 6 January 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url =  http://wbpspm.gov.in/publications/District%20Human%20Development%20Report |title =  District Human Development Report  | work=  Uttar Dinajpur. Page 14: Map showing locational setting of Uttar Dinajpur district (includes Dakshin Dinajpur district)|publisher= Department of Planning, Statistics and Programme Implementation, Government of West Bengal  | accessdate = 6 January 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nAt the [[1991 Bangladesh census]], Ranisankail had a population of 156107 inhabitants. Males constitute 51.67% of the population and females 48.33%. The number of adults was 76,136. Ranisankail had an average literacy rate of 25.7% (7+ years), below the national average of 32.4%.<ref name=\"census\">{{Cite web|  accessdate = November 10, 2006 |  url = http://www.bangladeshgov.org/mop/ndb/arpc91_v1/tables04.htm | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20050327072826/http://www.bangladeshgov.org/mop/ndb/arpc91_v1/tables04.htm | archivedate = 2005-03-27 | title = Population Census Wing, BBS.}}</ref>\n\nRanisankail (Town) consists of five mouzas. The area of the town is 13.94&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. The town has a population of 13521; male 52.09%, female 47.91%; population density per km<sup>2</sup> 970. Literacy rate among the town people is 36.9%.\n\nPopulation 156107; male 51.67%, female 48.33%. Muslim 76.23%, Hindu 22.79%, Christian 0.30% and others 0.98%; ethnic nationals: Santal 537 families.\nMain occupations Agriculture 53.7%, agricultural laborer 28.52%, wage laborer 2.59%, commerce 6.41%, service 2.41% and others 6.37%.\n\n==Economy==\nLand control - Among the peasants, 3.43% are landless, 14.01% marginal, 12.78% small, 64.59% intermediate and 5.19% rich; cultivable land per head 0.13 hectare.\n\n==Places of interest==\nRanisankail is not only known for its natural environment, but also for its historical places.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} They include the Khunia Dighi Memorial, Palace of King Tonko Nath, Ramrai Dighi (a pond covering 50 acres), Nekmord Oras mela (Fair of Nekmardon), Nekamard Shah Nasiruddin Mazar. Nekmarad Hat. Katihar Hat in Razore village (known for Hindu shib mondir, Rash mela, Extinct Maghi Mela), Kulic river, Gorkoi Nath mondir (Temple-900 Years old), Dharmagar, Banglagar, Shidassory Pond (sida Digi, Bhandagram), Ranisonkail Pilot High School, Ancient Primary School (100 years old) and Rautnagar hat.\n\n==Administration==\nIn Ranisankail there are one Pourasava covered 9 words and 9 Unions/Wards, 124 Mauzas/Mahallas, and 122 villages.\n* Chairman: Shariar Ajam Munna\n* Vice Chairman: Sohel Rana\n* Woman Vice Chairman: Most. Shefali Begum\n* City Meyor: Alamgir Sarker\n* [[Upazila Nirbahi Officer]] (UNO): Mousumi Afrida<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moestab.gov.bd/pmis/Forms/unolist.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-01-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226125127/http://www.moestab.gov.bd/pmis/Forms/unolist.php |archivedate=2012-02-26 }}</ref>\n\n==Transport==\nThere are some highway bus services from Dhaka to Ranisankail run by companies such as Hanif, Rozina, Shymoli, Banlu, AB Enterprise, Rahbar, AK Travels, Keya Poribahan,Dipjal,Diganta and others. Most of them go from Shamoly, Asadgate, Gabtoli of Dhaka. A bus trip from Dhaka to Ranisankail takes about 9\u201310 hours. Those buses go through Bangabandhu Jamuna bridge on the Dhaka to Thakurgaon highway road.\nOne BRTC bus give service from Ranisankail to Rajshahi\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nImage:Shibdhighi Tematha.JPG|Shibdhighi Three point at Ranisankail \nImage:Kulik River.JPG|Kulik River at westside of Ranisankail Upazila\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Thakurgaon District}}\n{{Upazilas of Rangpur Division}}\n\n[[Category:Upazilas of Thakurgaon District]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name           = Ranisonkail\n| native_name             = \u09b0\u09be\u09a3\u09c0\u09b6\u09a8\u0995\u09c8\u09b2\n| settlement_type         = [[Upazilas of Bangladesh|Upazila]]\n| image_skyline           =\n| imagesize               =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = Skyline of Ranisonkail, Bangladesh\n| pushpin_map             = Bangladesh\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Bangladesh\n| coordinates             = {{coord|25|{{#expr:.8875*60 round 1}}|N|88|{{#expr:.2514*